00:16:36,238 --> 00:16:45,602
You know, we know what happened to other Kohl's in the past, so I think we need more specifics on which actual days Kohl's is going to be open for 24 hours.

220
00:16:47,842 --> 00:16:49,903
Point of information, Counselor DelaRusso.

221
00:16:50,544 --> 00:16:57,166
Does the department store hire during the peak shopping periods internal store security?

222
00:16:58,527 --> 00:16:58,747
They do.

223
00:17:02,099 --> 00:17:02,339
Thank you.

224
00:17:02,559 --> 00:17:02,819
Thank you.

225
00:17:02,999 --> 00:17:03,600
Councilor Penta.

226
00:17:04,020 --> 00:17:10,082
Mr. President, I, I'm not satisfied over the fact that we're going to give this thing out in finitum because this is the first tryout.

227
00:17:10,663 --> 00:17:24,448
Um, regardless whether it's cold or anyone else, if you give it to them, it's going to set a precedent for any other type of store within the city of Medford department store or what have you claiming that the Christmas season, you know, it's going to be helpful to their business.

228
00:17:24,768 --> 00:17:31,371
I've got no problem and allowing it to go through for the first year and on an annual basis has just come back because if everything works out satisfactory,

229
00:17:31,684 --> 00:17:32,565
there should be no problem.

230
00:17:32,885 --> 00:17:48,077
But we're setting a precedent here to allow one department store, large as it might be, taxpayer as they might be, but there are a lot of small business folks here in the city of Medford, and they're taxpayers too, and they should be looked upon equally.

231
00:17:48,197 --> 00:18:01,048
And I just think we're setting a precedent here that we're not gonna be able to offset because if Coles gets it, three or four other people or five or six, no matter what part of the city they might be in, might be just coming down here.

232
00:18:01,801 --> 00:18:02,422
That's number one.

233
00:18:02,442 --> 00:18:03,522
You can go to Wellington Circle.

234
00:18:03,562 --> 00:18:06,384
You can go to the new mall down there.

235
00:18:06,484 --> 00:18:10,306
And I can see them wanting to operate and open during that period of time.

236
00:18:10,686 --> 00:18:15,809
Restaurants to accommodate businesses that are going to be open during that period of time to satisfy people.

237
00:18:16,450 --> 00:18:19,492
I've got no problem in having a designated amount of time.

238
00:18:19,512 --> 00:18:21,193
I have no problem allowing it for this year.

239
00:18:21,553 --> 00:18:23,314
I have no problem in giving the extended hours.

240
00:18:23,794 --> 00:18:29,638
But I am not in favor of making this a rule in perpetuity, to be honest with you.

241
00:18:30,760 --> 00:18:34,163
But I think one of the councilors has suggested a 90-day review.

242
00:18:34,403 --> 00:18:45,311
So the council would have the opportunity to review in 90 days whether or not there are any problems during this season, and assuming there is not, not require coals to come back again next year.

243
00:18:45,751 --> 00:18:49,114
If there are problems, then they could be addressed at the 90-day review time.

244
00:18:49,254 --> 00:18:55,419
Well, whether it's 90 days, or one day, or a year from now, the management of coals could be entirely different.

245
00:18:56,439 --> 00:18:59,482
Issues could take place after the 90 days that could present a problem.

246
00:19:00,966 --> 00:19:04,890
I just — listen, I've got no problem with it, but I just can't — to me, 90 days means nothing.

247
00:19:04,930 --> 00:19:07,792
I just think they should come in on an annual basis on a case-by-case.

248
00:19:08,153 --> 00:19:15,299
Because if we grant it for one, it's going to be very hard for us to be argued of being arbitrary and capricious and not allowing it to go to somebody else.

249
00:19:19,242 --> 00:19:22,225
The Press Thank you very much, Mr. President, and through you to the gentleman.

250
00:19:23,286 --> 00:19:28,130
Would Kohl's be amenable to providing the dates that they would like to be open?

251
00:19:29,095 --> 00:19:32,996
say maybe the day following Veterans Day to the Chief of Police, would that be enough time?

252
00:19:33,036 --> 00:19:33,296
Sure.

253
00:19:33,316 --> 00:19:35,816
I mean, I think we could specify now.

254
00:19:35,836 --> 00:19:39,877
It wouldn't be anything earlier than seven days prior to Christmas.

255
00:19:40,677 --> 00:19:55,140
So, I mean, if that's the kind of specificity that the council is looking for, you know, you know, between, between the dates of December 18th and December 25th, Black Friday plus, uh,

256
00:19:56,450 --> 00:19:59,012
up to seven days between December 18 and December 25.

257
00:19:59,133 --> 00:20:06,540
I mean, that's — those are specific dates, so — Mr. Rubinstein.

258
00:20:06,560 --> 00:20:07,581
Counselor De La Russo.

259
00:20:08,001 --> 00:20:09,963
Mr. President — December 24, obviously.

260
00:20:10,303 --> 00:20:20,813
The sad reality of retail in America is that it's become, unfortunately, common practice for retail stores of this magnitude

261
00:20:21,467 --> 00:20:24,208
to engage in these extended hours.

262
00:20:25,529 --> 00:20:32,152
We can perhaps spend another evening talking about how this is a commentary on society.

263
00:20:32,172 --> 00:20:33,432
I don't know.

264
00:20:34,093 --> 00:20:36,074
But that's not our purpose here.

265
00:20:37,174 --> 00:20:39,455
They've made a reasonable request of us.

266
00:20:40,416 --> 00:20:49,940
It's a matter that allows such a retail establishment to compete with peer stores to remain competitive.

267
00:20:51,088 --> 00:21:00,754
Maybe none of us like that idea that people are out shopping at 3 in the morning, but, you know, this is America.

268
00:21:02,255 --> 00:21:14,101
They've made a reasonable request, and also we've put very reasonable amendments to this request, one of them being a 90-day review.

269
00:21:14,822 --> 00:21:19,565
And so with regards to precedent-setting, at that point of 90 days,

270
00:21:20,658 --> 00:21:23,580
Well, it's all fresh in our minds, fresh after the holidays.

271
00:21:24,121 --> 00:21:26,302
We'll have them in here and review it.

272
00:21:26,983 --> 00:21:36,850
And if at that time that we want to limit it to four days, we can do that based on the experience of how this went during this holiday season.

273
00:21:37,371 --> 00:21:39,192
If at that time we say, you know what?

274
00:21:39,892 --> 00:21:41,374
This was nothing but a nightmare.

275
00:21:41,954 --> 00:21:43,495
We're not going to let it happen anymore.

276
00:21:43,515 --> 00:21:44,916
We're going to rescind this permission.

277
00:21:45,617 --> 00:21:49,880
Or my suspicion is that we're going to get to nine days and say,

278
00:21:50,627 --> 00:21:55,049
It went without any unexpected incident, and it may continue.

279
00:21:55,730 --> 00:22:01,353
So I think, again, I'd like to move the question as amended.

280
00:22:02,413 --> 00:22:03,514
Vice President Caravaglia.

281
00:22:03,794 --> 00:22:04,594
Thank you, Mr. President.

282
00:22:04,655 --> 00:22:06,616
I agree with my Councilor De La Rosa here.

283
00:22:07,216 --> 00:22:12,619
You know, the holiday season is a very important time for these stores.

284
00:22:12,639 --> 00:22:13,819
They've only got so many days.

285
00:22:14,140 --> 00:22:18,662
And now they're facing more competition from the new assembly mall.

286
00:22:19,490 --> 00:22:20,690
All the outlet stores over there.

287
00:22:21,711 --> 00:22:24,672
And I'm sure they're going to be open in the same hours as they are.

288
00:22:25,312 --> 00:22:30,654
And it's not fair to us to saddle these guys with these conditions.

289
00:22:32,715 --> 00:22:35,196
They said there's going to be no deliveries after a certain hour.

290
00:22:35,216 --> 00:22:36,276
They're going to have a policeman there.

291
00:22:36,296 --> 00:22:37,697
They're going to specify the days.

292
00:22:38,257 --> 00:22:47,080
And like I said, come 90 days, if it doesn't work out, then that'll be a story for next year.

293
00:22:48,210 --> 00:22:52,233
I feel it's unfair to say no to these people, and all the other cities and towns are doing it.

294
00:22:53,054 --> 00:22:56,536
And then we complain that all our people are going elsewhere.

295
00:22:57,476 --> 00:22:57,657
So.

296
00:22:58,837 --> 00:22:59,758
Councilor Langel-Kern.

297
00:23:00,218 --> 00:23:12,827
Just last, if we can move that as an amendment, what Attorney Bruzee said for Black Friday and seven days between December 18th and December 24th.

298
00:23:14,365 --> 00:23:15,786
Are you withdrawing your original motion?

299
00:23:16,026 --> 00:23:18,527
No, as well as notifying the chief specifically.

300
00:23:18,547 --> 00:23:20,669
Your original motion, councillor, was for five days.

301
00:23:22,270 --> 00:23:23,550
I didn't move that as an amendment.

302
00:23:23,590 --> 00:23:25,992
I just said I thought it was excessive.

303
00:23:26,032 --> 00:23:27,012
It was an amendment, so.

304
00:23:27,193 --> 00:23:29,374
Are you withdrawing that amendment for the new one?

305
00:23:29,794 --> 00:23:31,435
Yes, I don't believe I made that as an amendment, but.

306
00:23:31,775 --> 00:23:33,596
It was, the clerk has it written down as an amendment.

307
00:23:34,337 --> 00:23:37,298
So on the... Councillor?

308
00:23:37,739 --> 00:23:41,401
I think Attorney Bruese was amendable to eight days, which this covers.

309
00:23:41,922 --> 00:23:43,943
So maybe we can make it eight days rather than five.

310
00:23:44,183 --> 00:23:45,604
That's right.

311
00:23:45,624 --> 00:23:46,824
Total of eight.

312
00:23:46,844 --> 00:23:48,465
Total of eight.

313
00:23:48,765 --> 00:23:49,186
Total of eight.

314
00:23:49,226 --> 00:23:49,706
That's what I meant.

315
00:23:49,746 --> 00:23:49,866
Yep.

316
00:23:51,407 --> 00:23:54,428
Total of eight with the notification for the chief two weeks before.

317
00:23:55,249 --> 00:23:57,230
Is that our veterans day?

318
00:23:59,611 --> 00:24:00,071
Veterans day.

319
00:24:01,352 --> 00:24:01,552
Sure.

320
00:24:01,952 --> 00:24:02,112
Okay.

321
00:24:02,755 --> 00:24:04,516
On the motion, as amended.

322
00:24:04,996 --> 00:24:10,078
And a letter to the Meadow Glen Mall regarding deliveries that take place between 11 p.m.

323
00:24:10,098 --> 00:24:10,698
and 7 a.m.

324
00:24:10,718 --> 00:24:12,179
in the morning, other than Kohl's.

325
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:14,060
Yep.

326
00:24:14,080 --> 00:24:19,122
I want to send a letter to Austin to refrain from truck deliveries between those hours.

327
00:24:19,242 --> 00:24:19,582
We have that.

328
00:24:19,642 --> 00:24:20,763
On behalf of the neighbors.

329
00:24:21,703 --> 00:24:22,323
Councilor Penta.

330
00:24:24,304 --> 00:24:29,346
Some of the amendments I'm okay with, but I'm still concerned over the fact that you're going to review it in 90 days.

331
00:24:31,828 --> 00:24:44,035
I think if I was a proprietor in the Meadow Glen Mall right now, and I knew that they could be open during those particular hours, I think I'd be coming here next and just saying, well, I'd like to be open, because you just gave it to them.

332
00:24:44,055 --> 00:24:54,322
And if I was a food establishment in the Meadow Glen Mall as they are, I think they're going to come in here, and they're going to want extended hours to accommodate the people who are going to be possibly shopping all night long.

333
00:24:54,902 --> 00:24:59,425
And then if you go to Stations Landing, and if you want to go over there, and if those stores want to be open,

334
00:25:00,751 --> 00:25:01,991
I've got no problem with it.

335
00:25:02,011 --> 00:25:04,072
I don't understand why you just have to give it.

336
00:25:05,132 --> 00:25:07,893
Why can't we just give it out for this first year and see where this goes?

337
00:25:08,053 --> 00:25:12,975
See how many other people want to apply for this 24—I mean, they're trailblazing right now.

338
00:25:13,015 --> 00:25:15,276
They're setting the trademark as to what they want to do.

339
00:25:15,676 --> 00:25:17,076
And let's just see how many other people come in.

340
00:25:17,836 --> 00:25:29,640
It'd be a shame to have somebody come in here and want to have the exact same thing, and they get shot down because, quote-unquote, either the neighbors or someone, you know, want to object to it because they don't want to be disturbed during those particular hours.

341
00:25:31,629 --> 00:25:33,370
You can put all the amendments you want onto this thing.

342
00:25:33,671 --> 00:25:34,892
That's the only thing that bothers me.

343
00:25:35,212 --> 00:25:47,803
You know, I just don't think you should be able to give it out in perpetuity, because if you give it out in perpetuity, and if you bring it back in 90 days, and for whatever the problems, and even if there were problems, and you were going to address them, they still have the thing in perpetuity.

344
00:25:47,863 --> 00:25:58,211
And to get rid of that, as both attorneys know, it's going to be pretty hard, because you haven't specifically laid down rules that could cancel out that rule of perpetuity while they're extended forever.

345
00:25:59,577 --> 00:26:07,203
I've got no problem voting for it, but I want to amend it that it just become, on an annual basis, a first-time basis, and let's just see where we go with this.

346
00:26:07,743 --> 00:26:08,584
It's as simple as that.

347
00:26:09,184 --> 00:26:09,925
That is an amendment?

348
00:26:10,325 --> 00:26:11,086
Yes.

349
00:26:11,866 --> 00:26:18,932
The amendment is in direct contrast with the paper, so we're going to take a separate vote on Councilor Penta's amendment first, and then we'll take the paper as amended.

350
00:26:19,532 --> 00:26:22,574
On Councilor Penta's amendment, all those in favor?

351
00:26:22,594 --> 00:26:23,515
Aye.

352
00:26:23,875 --> 00:26:24,596
All those opposed?

353
00:26:24,776 --> 00:26:25,417
Roll call vote.

354
00:26:25,777 --> 00:26:26,938
Roll call has been requested.

355
00:26:28,274 --> 00:26:30,495
A yes vote is for Councilor Penta's amendment.

356
00:26:30,595 --> 00:26:36,198
A no vote is to take a vote on the paper as amended prior to his proposal.

357
00:26:41,381 --> 00:26:42,741
Annual rather than perpetuity.

358
00:26:42,941 --> 00:26:44,862
Yes is to have it just this one year.

359
00:26:45,323 --> 00:26:47,444
A no vote will be the original intent of the paper.

360
00:26:49,925 --> 00:26:50,565
Councilor Marks.

361
00:26:51,185 --> 00:26:54,247
I want to understand my Councilor colleague's comments.

362
00:26:55,393 --> 00:27:02,875
Why would you think it would be so difficult for us to rescind the perpetuity that allows them to do it every year automatically?

363
00:27:02,915 --> 00:27:05,015
Why would that be so difficult by a vote of the kind?

364
00:27:05,215 --> 00:27:07,156
Just say in a year, two years from now, we say, you know what?

365
00:27:07,496 --> 00:27:10,376
Even after the 90-day review, we no longer like this.

366
00:27:10,576 --> 00:27:11,296
What's the reason?

367
00:27:11,456 --> 00:27:12,197
Point of information.

368
00:27:13,417 --> 00:27:15,297
Point of information, Counselor De La Russo.

369
00:27:15,497 --> 00:27:18,218
Is perpetuity the proper legal term to this?

370
00:27:18,358 --> 00:27:19,878
Is this granted in perpetuity?

371
00:27:19,918 --> 00:27:20,838
No, it's indefinite.

372
00:27:21,279 --> 00:27:22,219
Or is it indefinite?

373
00:27:22,259 --> 00:27:22,679
Indefinite.

374
00:27:22,819 --> 00:27:23,399
Indefinitely.

375
00:27:24,346 --> 00:27:25,847
Because there's a difference in the word.

376
00:27:25,947 --> 00:27:29,109
Imperfectuity is... Forever.

377
00:27:29,549 --> 00:27:32,451
Forever and ever, till the Lord walks on this earth again.

378
00:27:33,032 --> 00:27:37,654
So I don't think that's in anything that we give.

379
00:27:39,175 --> 00:27:40,416
Thank you for your clarification.

380
00:27:41,357 --> 00:27:41,837
Councilor Marks.

381
00:27:42,998 --> 00:27:44,739
My question was to my colleague.

382
00:27:44,799 --> 00:27:45,639
Why you would think that?

383
00:27:45,659 --> 00:27:47,821
Because this is the first time this is appearing before us.

384
00:27:48,801 --> 00:27:51,663
And I think being for the first time, let's just see how it goes.

385
00:27:52,482 --> 00:28:07,352
I'm not about to give away the store on the very first time somebody comes here and then have another person come and get denied because maybe they just don't cut the same—it's not cut the same way, whether it's their neighbors, whether it's the neighborhood, whether it's the location or what have you.

386
00:28:07,912 --> 00:28:15,597
I can just see other people wanting to have the same issue, have the same argument, and I've got no problem with that, and I think we should address them one at a time.

387
00:28:17,072 --> 00:28:19,094
Give it to them for the first year, I've got no problem with that.

388
00:28:19,174 --> 00:28:23,177
Even if you want to review it after 90 days, cut it to five, call the police chief, chief of police.

389
00:28:23,578 --> 00:28:29,162
And if everything works out great, and the gentleman in the back there, they have no problems, they come back again next year, it shouldn't present a problem.

390
00:28:30,163 --> 00:28:31,604
But what are we going to do in the meantime?

391
00:28:31,945 --> 00:28:39,271
I ask all of you, if company X comes in now, and they want the same thing, what are we going to do?

392
00:28:39,311 --> 00:28:43,875
Honestly, I think we have to base every request on its own merits.

393
00:28:44,607 --> 00:28:56,071
And you're right, if it was a business that was nestled in a neighborhood that wanted to open 24 hours, I would look upon it differently than a business that's in a mall establishment.

394
00:28:56,511 --> 00:29:05,874
And even the abutter stated that the front entrance would really have no bearing, people coming through the front entrance, on their sleep and so forth in the buildings.

395
00:29:06,294 --> 00:29:09,696
So I think you have to take every petition on its own merits.

396
00:29:10,616 --> 00:29:13,497
But my question was just whether or not

397
00:29:14,358 --> 00:29:17,762
and a year from now that we as a council can rescind this vote.

398
00:29:18,222 --> 00:29:23,568
And I believe we can do that like on any Tuesday night, and I don't think it's a difficult process.

399
00:29:23,608 --> 00:29:27,934
And if this didn't work out for whatever reason, I'm willing to take a vote to rescind.

400
00:29:30,593 --> 00:29:31,494
Thank you, Counselor Marks.

401
00:29:31,594 --> 00:29:35,297
If I may, from the chair, I hear what both counselors are saying.

402
00:29:35,697 --> 00:29:42,683
Would the attorney be amenable to, every year, a 90-day review, just in case there's not a mob rush three, four years from now?

403
00:29:42,783 --> 00:29:48,067
We'll just review it after 90 days as a council, and if there's no, basically put the 90-day review.

404
00:29:48,127 --> 00:29:49,769
I guess I'm not sure how that would work.

405
00:29:49,809 --> 00:29:52,971
I mean, what I want to avoid is the necessity to come back every year.

406
00:29:53,472 --> 00:29:57,315
I'm completely comfortable with the council reviewing this.

407
00:29:58,337 --> 00:30:02,819
you know, in 90 days and see how it went as Councilor DelaRusso went.

408
00:30:03,440 --> 00:30:06,561
I'd also like to point out that, I mean, we're not being trailblazers here.

409
00:30:06,781 --> 00:30:10,844
There are a number of establishments that are open 24 hours a day now.

410
00:30:11,044 --> 00:30:11,964
You have Stop and Shop.

411
00:30:11,984 --> 00:30:15,906
You have a number of 24-hour permits, correct, Mr. Clerk?

412
00:30:15,966 --> 00:30:16,747
Correct me if I'm wrong.

413
00:30:16,767 --> 00:30:18,848
So we're not being a trailblazer here.

414
00:30:19,028 --> 00:30:24,951
This is... But they've closed at 11 because of the business.

415
00:30:26,720 --> 00:30:30,343
And we will be closing at 9 or 10 o'clock, 358 days a year.

416
00:30:39,001 --> 00:30:41,083
The first vote is on the amendment of Councilor Penta.

417
00:30:41,143 --> 00:30:45,706
A yes vote is for Councilor Penta's amendment.

418
00:30:45,746 --> 00:30:48,769
A no vote is... Well, the amendment... Tell them what the amendment is.

419
00:30:48,789 --> 00:30:55,394
The amendment is to have... The amendment... Councilor Penta's amendment is to have this as a trial this year and this year only.

420
00:30:55,894 --> 00:30:56,455
A yes vote.

421
00:30:56,535 --> 00:31:01,799
A no vote will be for the paper as presented, as amended by the Medford City Council up to this point.

422
00:31:02,379 --> 00:31:05,442
Before I call the roll, we have a gentleman in the audience that would like to speak, I guess.

423
00:31:12,632 --> 00:31:14,893
Andrew Castanetti, Cushing Street Method Mass.

424
00:31:15,733 --> 00:31:21,414
I hate to go against the man upstairs, and once upon a time there were blue laws in this state.

425
00:31:22,954 --> 00:31:28,936
However, as one of the councilors stated, it's the state of the times, it's capitalism, so to speak.

426
00:31:29,976 --> 00:31:32,677
It's been a long discussion.

427
00:31:34,617 --> 00:31:41,839
I believe in the spirit of compromise, especially with council, they're making some great points.

428
00:31:43,810 --> 00:31:53,433
Maybe you people might want to consider a one-shot deal, and for eight days as a compromise.

429
00:31:54,854 --> 00:31:58,475
And then you don't have to worry about 90-day review.

430
00:31:58,495 --> 00:32:00,776
It can come back next year.

431
00:32:03,077 --> 00:32:12,580
Because if it becomes an issue after 90 days or prior to 90 days, unfortunately, this country is strong on litigation.

432
00:32:13,237 --> 00:32:14,879
