1755
02:09:16,450 --> 02:09:18,472
So I did seek out that answer because I was

1756
02:09:19,834 --> 02:09:22,875
Didn't know the answer last week, so that is where it is.

1757
02:09:25,616 --> 02:09:26,356
Councilor Marks.

1758
02:09:27,016 --> 02:09:27,996
Thank you, Mr. President.

1759
02:09:28,196 --> 02:09:39,079
And also, last week, the issue of the South Method neighborhood safety walk was brought up to a resolution offered by myself.

1760
02:09:39,860 --> 02:09:42,380
And we had a number of South Method residents here.

1761
02:09:43,100 --> 02:09:48,322
And at the time, it was mentioned that there was a violation

1762
02:09:48,855 --> 02:09:55,037
of the open meeting law if more than four members of the council attended this particular meeting.

1763
02:09:55,857 --> 02:10:07,520
And where part of my resolution was to try to expand this particular safety walk, I sent an email to the city solicitor and also the city clerk.

1764
02:10:08,140 --> 02:10:14,581
And I believe we all got a response back via email from the city solicitor, Mark Rumley.

1765
02:10:15,141 --> 02:10:17,522
And I just would like to read it for the edification of

1766
02:10:18,219 --> 02:10:30,548
people that may be watching, I don't want anyone to believe that there was any doubt that there was no violation of the open meeting law at this neighborhood walk.

1767
02:10:30,908 --> 02:10:45,739
But it says, dear Councilor Marks, you have asked me whether the attendance of city councilors at an event organized by a private citizen group for the purpose of addressing neighborhood safety and other related concerns could potentially be a violation of the open meeting law.

1768
02:10:46,239 --> 02:10:47,660
My answer is that the attendance

1769
02:10:48,090 --> 02:10:52,453
by City Council is at such an event would not be a violation of the Open Meeting Law.

1770
02:10:52,994 --> 02:10:59,299
The basis for my conclusion is that General Law Chapter 38, the Open Meeting Law applies to public bodies.

1771
02:11:00,079 --> 02:11:13,510
According to the facts you have presented to me, the neighborhood safety walk was organized by a private citizen group and was neither scheduled by the City Council nor was it subject to the Council's direction or control.

1772
02:11:14,050 --> 02:11:15,952
It was therefore essentially an opportunity

1773
02:11:16,427 --> 02:11:26,795
for the participants, including the counselors, to observe conditions in a particular neighborhood rather than to make decisions through a vote of a quorum or the city council.

1774
02:11:27,516 --> 02:11:32,980
Even though the private citizen group that called for the walk was concerned with public issues, i.e.

1775
02:11:33,061 --> 02:11:44,670
neighborhood safety and related issues, it is not a public body as it is not an entity within the executive or legislative branches of state government or within any county, district, city, region, or town.

1776
02:11:45,182 --> 02:11:46,423
I hope this answers your opinion.

1777
02:11:46,844 --> 02:11:47,965
Respectfully, Mark Rumley.

1778
02:11:48,565 --> 02:11:49,906
Thank you very much, Councillor Marks.

1779
02:11:50,067 --> 02:11:57,053
And also, I'm glad you brought this up because the Attorney General's office is actually the oversight authority on this particular matter now.

1780
02:11:57,454 --> 02:12:03,199
It used to be the District Attorney's office, but within the last four or five years, it changed under the jurisdiction of the AG's office.

1781
02:12:03,740 --> 02:12:13,523
And the AG's office, if anyone wants to call them, if any deliberations or anything come up at a meeting, whether it's public body or not, it could be constitute a violation.

1782
02:12:14,003 --> 02:12:24,046
So I know at your meeting there was no deliberations, but even talking about something that maybe the council has jurisdiction over, and I'm glad you asked the question to the city solicitor though.

1783
02:12:24,446 --> 02:12:31,028
But any further questions, you can ask the Attorney General's office, who is the authority, and they will give guidance to any public body.

